This has to be the cleanest, nicest laundromat in LA.

The woman who runs this place reminds me of my grandmother. I just want to give her a hug after I do my laundry.

< Text>
I went to a different mortgage place at the beginning of 2017 and I didn't feel like I was being taken seriously. I'm someone who has many questions and I like to get answers to those questions but all the answers I was getting felt confusing and my goals seemed unobtainable. So, I left that office with my tail between my legs. I spoke to my husband about seeing Benji but because I was so discouraged I waited 8 months to do so. I'm so glad I finally made the appointment with him!

First off, I LOVED that I could request an appoint online. I don't have much time during working hours to spend on the phone so that feature was extremely convenient. His secretary got back to me within a couple hours and scheduled me an appointment by email. When I arrived for my appointment I immediately noticed how cozy it felt. His receptionist was very kind and offered me a drink (water, soda, etc.). Meeting Benji for the first time I immediately felt comfortable talking to him. He answered all my questions in terms I could understand. My husband came to the appointment a little late and Benji had no problem filling him in on things we discussed. Benji gave us something the person before him didn't. HOPE! We left there feeling like would could really do this! We could really own a home soon!
Benji replied to all my messages in an extremely timely manner and never made me feel like I was pestering him.

Soon after we met Mike who was also very warm and kind. He explained everything clearly and also answered all my stupid questions without hesitation. We left our appointment with him feeling like we had made a new friend. Lynn, the loan processor Mike assigned to us, is also very kind. She is extremely prompt. I try to gather and send out paperwork within a 24 hour period of it being requested and everyone I've dealt with during this process works just as quickly.

This entire office has made this stressful experience extremely easy going. I'm overly happy my husband and I decided to use Benji and his team and since day one we've been telling EVERYONE to make an appointment with him.< /Text>

{'time': 1471123465722, 'text': "I'm glad your buying experience with me went well.  Unfortunately, when we pre-approve clients they bring us in requested tax returns.  Until the buyers go into contract on a house, we don't know if they have officially been filed until we get form 4506t from the IRS as a verification lenders are required to get during escrow.  We called your agent within the first week and explained the issue.  And yes, it was unfortunately the buyer bought 2 cars during escrow, but please tell me how I as the lender am responsible for a client purchasing cars during escrow?  It's easy to blame the lender and give a 1 star and that's unfortunate.  I'm glad you sold your house and everything worked out.  Not all clients have perfect credit and in this case, make the best decisions during eacrow.  I will gladly own up to issues our office does as we aren't perfect, but in no way will we take responsibility for a client giving us 2015 returns but not actually filing them nor financing 2 cars during escrow.  Again, I'm glad you sold your house and I'm sorry that your first buyers didn't work out, but A 1 star rating doesn't seem justified.  I would be the first to admit if we screwed up, but on this one, absolutely not.  Thanks again"}< /resp>

< Review>
After reading the website and speaking with a representative at the 1-800 number I must admit that I was skeptical. I couldn't quite believe that I could be examined, have teeth extracted and walk out with partials or full dentures in the same day. It happened though. The people there made me feel comfortable right away and provided me with all the information that I needed. I highly recommend this facility to anyone needing some new teeth.< /Review>

I was impressed by the professional staff that thoroughly explained what could be done with my case.  I went in there thinking there wasn't much hope for my situation.  The assistant to the dentist, April, was so knowledgeable and experienced with similar patients, that she assured me I was not a hopeless case and there was a solution. <text>They did a great job with my dentures. I'm completely satisfied with the results. Natural looking, perfect proportions‚Äã and a great fit.
I would recommend this place to anyone looking for quality and a reasonable price.
Updated , after 3 years my dentures were due to be relined.   The office in Redding had recently gotten a new phone system,  and,  the website lists the corporate number instead of the one for that office...I booked the appointment a week ahead,  then when I was going to be a little late because of the train crossing being blocked, I tried to call and let them know that I was on my way.  The call was answered by someone at corporate office, who told me that there was no appointment,  it had been canceled!
I was already on the road, so I went to the office and managed to get in after a short wait. That part was OK. However, I don't think they were on top of their game after being closed for so long (COVID19).
The lining was a bit shabby, not enough time taken to polish it out,  which resulted in considerable pain for me. It feels like there are fine grains of sand embedded . Very painful and disappointing.  I have no choice but to go back again to see what can be done!
Next day...the woman that took my impressions both times is wonderful. It was a little bit busy, of course, but she polished it out and I am now 100% satisfied...<//text><pictures>None< /pictures>< Resp>

Chose this place because the dentists where I live were unable to get me in for the work I needed, not to save money. At that time the reviews i found were favorable, although a recent search has shown that that has changed drastically. Paid up front for full service. Li Hou barely speaks English, which wouldn't be a problem if she was actually trying to listen to you, which she isn't. She is downright violent in her handling, acts put out by your very presence, wields her hands like seal clubs, egotistical to the extreme. They will not make appointments for basic adjustments and checkups that were already paid for. Teeth literally fall out if i open my mouth, and do not align in a way that makes it possible to eat. At one point she even flipped out and started yelling at me because she misunderstood a suggestion that she MAY have made a mistake, and told me to leave her office and not come back... Which she retracted fairly quickly once i began recording her insane ego rant and threatened a lawsuit. have been screwed around with by them for a year and two months, at enormous cost(17k), and still don't have working teeth... really, haven't eaten a solid meal in over a year. May see her in court. I feel insulted, disrespected, hurt and hungry. Spare yourself and anybody you care about the hell of this facility. The only good thing I have to say is that the assistant April is one of the most friendly and caring professionals one could imagine, although she has no real authority. I hope she gets work someplace more respectable and humane. Li Hou is, in short, a monster and a quack.< /Review>

After we sat there in the waiting room for almost two hours, they finally came and took me to one of the rooms to wait for the dentist. <review>I stopped by this location yesterday a little after 5 AM to get breakfast and coffee before my appointment across the road with Stanford Cancer Center. I commend the location and the early morning staff for strictly following proper social distancing measures. Although this review is not only meant to praise the cleanliness and the safety feeling it gives their  patrons but particularly about the young lady who greeted me at the door. All three staff had a pretty good system where one was the runner (the lady greeter), the second staff (male) was the dedicated barista for the day and the third staff (female) was manning the cash register and helping out at the kitchen. Obviously, customers weren‚Äôt allowed beyond the makeshift barrier they have provided as you enter the door. Unfortunately the cash register and the app scanner was understandably located in its original location which was behind the makeshift barrier.
So in order for my app to be scanned, the lady runner has to bring my phone over to the scanner.  The staff saw that I was not comfortable with the idea because I didn‚Äôt see the runner change gloves after she helped the customer before me. I was trying to explain why I was feeling uncomfortable and apologetic at the same time, telling them that I am an immuno compromised cancer patient. The lady cashier immediately dismissed me by saying that I can always go to another store. I got all flustered  because I was thinking I didn‚Äôt have my sani wipes available because I knew that I did not need to touch anything except for my order and I just wanted my coffee and breakfast.
The next scene is how I find the lady runner‚Äôs response highly commendable. After hearing about my condition, she immediately offered to wash her hands and change gloves to which my knee jerk response was, ‚Äúyes please‚Äù. Without saying a word, she did oblige while the cashier was mumbling a comment to the barista and shaking her head.
At that moment I felt embarrassed because I realized she didn‚Äôt need to wash her hands, she just needed to change her plastic gloves and yet she went above and beyond what was expected of her. That‚Äôs great customer service right there! I wanted to go back and ask for her name but I didn‚Äôt want to give her the wrong impression. Obviously this lady was trained well and  was putting her professional training to good use. She remembers her core values and knew how to practice them as a means to de-escalate the situation. God bless her for doing such a great job and may she be recognized as a valuable employee of Starbucks!< /review><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< response>

< Review>
I had their classic 'Big Ol' sammich. Yes, it's HUGE!! Check out my photo...I have HUGE hands. Super delicious! The perfect amount of crunch and spiciness. Their sauces are mild, medium, and hot. <Rate>2</Rate>< review>
I was excited to try this place since I've never had a Nashville chicken sandwich but was let down. I had gotten the HOT Big ol' Sandwich. The tender breading just tasted like slightly spicy breading, it was less heat than buffalo wings, maybe comparable to eating a bag of Hot Cheetos.. The meat itself was plain and had parts of tendon in it which made it so I had to tug to fully separate a piece. The bun was really good though. Pickles were soft and mushy. Coleslaw was okay as well. I'm not the biggest fan of coleslaw but I didn't mind eating it in the sandwich. The biggest reason why I rate this low is because there was a chunk of bone in one of the tenders.

I'll come back again and try something else. I always give places 2nd chances. But for now this wasn't a good first experience.

Order was placed 8/18/20. Around 2:10 PM.< /review>

<user_name>Alxs Grlr<//user_name>< Date>
1573663545824</Date>
<Rating>2<//Rating>< Text>
The chicken was great, but the service was not. If you'd like to sit and wait 30+ minutes in a restaurant with register staff that make you feel unwelcome, this is the place! I wanted to love this spot as I am a big fan of all fried chicken, but from the moment I walked in and began placing my order I was made to feel really uncomfortable by the girl at the register.

She was very rude- she didn't smile, and when I asked her a question about the menu she seemed irritated. I almost wanted to leave before finishing placing my order because it was THAT bad.

Then, after I placed my order (a plate of sliders) I ended up waiting for quite a long time. Several other tables of people that came in after me, were all served before me.

When I finally got my sliders, the Hawaiian bun was so soggy, it was practically mush. You could tell the food had been sitting for a while before they brought it out. Plus, they asked me for my receipt before they would serve me the food- something that usually shouldn't happen when you're dining-in (and they actually didn't give me a receipt to begin with).

I recommend they hire some friendlier staff to work in the front so that customers actually want to return. The food is good, but the service is a major factor in the entire experience, which is why I am rating only 2 stars.

Edit: I usually do not review places, I simply don't go again- but the experience I had at FireBirds was so unfortunate I felt it was necessary to write a review so that they know there's a problem with the register staff.<//Text>

<text>This place is still new, so it has some room for improvement. But the things they've got right are worth trying. It's a small menu, very fried chicken focused. We ordered the big ol' sandwich, fries, fried pickles and the fire birds mac and cheese. Both entrees had freshly prepared fried chicken breast. You can choose the heat level for the sandwich which is added to the breading. The mac and cheese is solid, pasta is cooked well and not so cheesy that it masks the chicken flavor. They give you a ton of fries and pickle chips in the orders. We barely made a dent in either of them. Pepsi products on the fountain.

<Name>Zac Burnside</Name><pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPC6ilvOYdUkFNrY4jxQuQjgqWxytHhmaJMHDdE=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOuK9ocYCEjAIEgp3bRJwfn7M8fqoMxr7v8XLET=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /pics><Text>Great spice blend! Firebirds has checked a bunch of boxes for what is missing in San Diego's hot chicken scene (which is mostly non-existent).
1. The chicken is juicy and well cooked.
2. The breading and spices are complex and enjoyable.
3. The portion size is on the larger side for the cost.
4. Spicier heat levels actually contain some heat.

Now the downsides.
1. The parking can be a challenge. There is a parking lot behind the building, but it's shared.
2. The fries were under-cooked. Maybe this is a one off instance, but this needs to be managed. Consistency is key for success.
3. The neighborhood is a bit to be desired, but this isn't a big knock. Gotta start somewhere.
4. The heat levels do not go high enough. The maximum heat level was a medium-hot on the Howlin Ray's menu.

All things considered, this is now the best hot chicken place in SD. Do yourself a favor and give it your attention!<//Text></record></dataset><record>

<Review>Ate here a while back, now time for a review.

Gf and I ordered a Big Ol' Sandwich, Firebird Mac & Cheese, and Deep Fried Pickles.

The Big Ol' was good, altho at a time when places are jumping on the chicken sandwich wave it couldn't quite place among the top. Fries were good. The Firebird Mac was probably the best of the three. Very filling. Deep fried chicken with shelled noodles .The Fried Pickles aren't on the standard menu, but a seasonal item? I'm not a pickle person, but my gf is, and she loved it. I'll have to take her word. :) Those did take a while to come out, the only reason I could think is that they were doing it from scratch?

The cashier was friendly and thorough. Apparently we had hit a good time (sometime between 3 and 4pm) because once we say down the line doubled. We couldn't finish all the food, which was well portioned. Perhaps only 2 items instead of 3 would have been perfect.

Would definitely come back. Gotta try a hotter sauce next time too.</Review></record></dataset><record>

< Text>
I had such high hopes. This rating is reflective of their customer service, quality of food and overall impression.

Positives:
-Reasonably priced
-Value based food

Middle of the road:
-Taste and quality of food (the best part of the sliders were the Hawaiian bread bun. They did not make them, so I can't give them full credit)

Fell short/Negatives:
-Staff - they were yelling at each other across the restaurant while customers walked in between. Overall they were blunt and unprofessional. When I left, no one said goodbye. They weren't warm. They seemed uninterested in their jobs. This is a new establishment. I would think the owner would like their customers greeted with a smile.
-Music: when I was there they turned on music that was LOUD. Left with ears hurting. The most unfortunate part was when a customer called in, and the employee continued to tell into the phone : "I CANT HEAR YOU, YOU NEED TO SPEAK UP". I yelled to my friend sitting directly across from me, that we needed to leave. He didn't hear me. I texted him.

I'll try to check back in a few weeks to see if things are improved. But with Crack Shack, Shake Shack and chik fil a proving solid customer service and amazing food it'll be difficult.

Advice: continue the solid food. Ensure all menu items are available. Train staff of better customer service.  Play music at a reasonable sound level.< /Text>

< Review>
Great Car! Great  Experience!!!  See Jason Galvan at Tustin Hyundai if you want to have an exceptional car buying experience! . From the moment we talked, I liked him. He was informative, helpful and enthusiastic.  There was absolutely no pressure on buying. His focus was to answer our questions and share as much information about the car as possible. In addition, he was personable, friendly, and made every effort to exceed my expectations.
When we decided to move forward on buying our Kona Electric, Jason's follow up and follow through was exceptional. He stayed in constant communication, found me the car (trim and color) I wanted and was able to facilitate the delivery quickly. On the day we finalized the deal ... and the days after, he has continued to be available and supportive in answering questions.
I also liked their finance manager, Crystal.  Helpful , informative and accommodating.  Midway in the process I requested additional miles and she quickly reworked the contract.
I have purchased many cars over the years, and I can honestly say this was one of the most stress free and fun experiences.</Review>

<rating>5<//rating><user_id>102853008930068306770<//user_id><text>My wife and I purchased an exceptionally well-kept, used 4Runner. The day I found it on the internet and called, Marcos Rodriguez from sales took my call and reported that the car was being readied for sale. Marcos was professional and politely said the car was being prepped for sale and that he would call me back as soon as it was ready. He kept his word and promptly sent me photos of the car a few days later on the  morning it was ready for sale.  We ended up driving about an hour to the dealership and purchased the car that same day after the used car manager, Gary Bagby, was willing to discount the price to help us meet our budget. The car had been detailed inside and out and the engine bay looked very clean. The interior smelled great and still does! The whole buying process went very smoothly.  We left very happy. About 3 weeks later, we discovered that all four tire pressure sensors needed to be replaced.    I was afraid that we were going to have to make the 1-hour drive to the  dealership and then have to argue why not just one sensor needed replacement but all four.  I called ahead and spoke with Martin Aguilar, the  service manager, and explained what Pep Boys and Costco Tire had told me about all sensors needing replacement. Working with Gary, the used car manager, Martin allowed me to get the sensors replaced close to home, saving me the drive to the dealership and  reimbursed me for the cost of replacing the sensors. They kept their promise of honoring the 30 day used car warranty without any hassle and they made it very convenient for me to get the repair done close to my home instead of using up what would have taken at least half a day had I been required to take the car back to the dealership. I made an online appointment for an ABS module inspection/replacement recall on my 2014 Santa Fe Sport. When I arrived for my 11:30 AM appointment on Wednesday, the service advisor I chose for my appointment (Bryan) was not available, so Martin took care of me. Martin was professional, truthful, and I've known him for over 10 years. I asked how long I have to wait and he said at least two hours. I also asked if I could use a $25 service coupon mailed to me from Hyundai corporate for an oil change. Martin didn't recognize the coupon, said that coupon is not eligible for my car due to different VIN (probably previous Hyundai I owned), and warned an oil change would add at least 30 more minutes to my wait time. I couldn't wait over 2.5 hours and noticed Tustin Hyundai has raised the price on the oil change from $39 to $47 now, so I passed on the oil change. I asked if the technician can top off my car's fluids and Martin wrote it down my request on the repair order. After Martin finished writing me up, he said Bryan will call me when my car is ready. The 2.5 hour wait time for a recall appointment seemed long, but the service department seemed very busy with a long line of cars waiting for service on the lot and cars constantly coming in and out. When Martin finally drove me car off the parking lot to the back, I asked him how much longer is my wait and he said he was still waiting for his guy to come back from lunch. My car spent more time sitting on the service parking lot than actually getting the recall done. Fortunately, Costco was across the street so I went there to do some shopping while I waited. When I finished shopping, I called the service department for a status update, but both Martin and Bryan were not available, so Trina helped me check status and told me my car was ready for pickup. I think my car was washed. The windows had wipe streaks, but I could still see some yellow bird poop specks on the hood that didn't wash off. The whole recall service took two hours as promised. Restroom was clean and stocked. And, I saw some complimentary snacks and candies by the cashier. When I started my car to drive home, I noticed the clock's date and time was reset and the radio's default display looked different than before, especially when I change radio stations. I guess part of the recall involved getting the software flashed.<//review>

<review>Update: Added a star because Trina, the customer relations manager, reached out to me immediately to discuss the experience I had last week. She was apologetic, sincere, and understands the importance of great customer service.

I had a decent experience at Tustin Hyundai. In the beginning, I do not think the sales representatives took me seriously (I do look a bit young for my actual age) about buying a car. I initially left because of it. When I returned solely because of the cars available, I honestly felt that I wasn't treated with respect until my credit check was completed. All I can say about that is for future sale opportunities, never judge a book by its cover. Also, during any business transaction, I expect the sales representative to be honest to the best of their ability. Unfortunately, it seemed like the team I dealt with was more concerned with making a sale as opposed to giving me honest quotes about how much my trade in car was worth. < review>
This is specifically for the Service Department. I've been to a couple Hyundai dealerships in OC & this is by far my best experience. I had to take in my car today for a simple oil change but I noticed they had a minor service special so I did that(good price) & they were the only dealership in my area offering that. I made the appointment online & was pleased to see they had available slots open this same afternoon. I checked in & was told the process was going to take about an hour (which was accurate). Upon receiving my car, I was told everything else was fine, they washed my car and what really put me over the top was that they replaced one of my signal lights that was out! Free of charge! I know the bulb itself must not cost much , so to them it wasn't a big deal but the fact that I didn't have to ask them or had even mentioned it really WOW-Ed me. Overall, great experience & I really appreciate the quick & efficient service they provided. Will definitely be coming back!<//review>

<UserId.>106397222405259680399< /UserId.>< Review>
They are OK ... if you are OK with grey or black cars, that is - seems like they don't stock any "fun" colors. These are middle-aged/older low-key down-to-earth guys ... selling cars with no gimmicks or add-ons ... at an average price. Same for the trade-in. The location itself is rather grim and bland. Then again, we came to buy a car not to be entertained. Do watch out for some minor tricks - they will try and pull your credit regardless of your having been pre-approved elsewhere. Therefore ... under no circumstances give them your DOB or SSN unless you really want them to finance you. Also ... make sure they prep the car appropriately - including checking the tire pressure and cleaning the interior. The bottom line: this is a pretty straight-forward dealership. Come here if you want to save time ... while not expecting the best deal.<//Review>

<Gmap_id>0x80dcdb89ab96aedd:0x2ef0260515d0404b</Gmap_id>< Text>
I obtained a new car lease on a Sonata Hybrid.
Rooben K. was the sales pro that I engaged with.
He was helpful in explaining the details, we went for a test drive, and he then organized a good price on the lease.
They didn't have a car with the exterior and internal combo I was after, so they got a car brought in within hours on the same day.
The finance application was also quite efficient, with all paperwork ready and no aggressive pitching of 15 different types of add-ons or warranties (as I had to sit through on my prior lease at another company/dealer).
All of the financial paper was done in around 15 minutes.
My new car had been fully detailed, and was waiting for me in the shade.
Rooben even wanted to put a big ribbon on the car, and I had to tell him that this was not necessary at all.
Rooben then spent time walking me through how everything worked in the car, making sure that I was completely comfortable with everything.
Very nice experience overall.</Text>

<Time>1555285893135</Time><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNAKWU9sVEzULXABAEvn4u1OeHBywv4eji5ekN4=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pics>< Review>
I was looking to buy a new 2019 Hyundai Veloster. I had found a couple new ones and was about to make a deal on one when I downloaded TrueCar. After a quick search, I found a 2019 Hyundai Veloster Turbo with 3,500 miles located in Tustin, CA (about an hour away from where I live in San Diego). I put the deal I had on hold and made plans to drive to Tustin Hyundai the next morning.

Before I had even closed the TrueCar app, Bill Farris, Internet Sales Consultant for Tustin Hyundai, had called me. I made arrangements to meet him the following day to test drive a white 2019 Hyundai Veloster.

Even though I had driven brand new one, I wanted to make sure this was the right car for me. Bill took me on a drive that allowed me to feel how the car handled and demonstrate its key benefits. The car, along with a much better price than a brand new one, sold me, but it was working with Bill that made it excellent.

Because I was making a cash deal, we had an agreement where payment would be delivered two days later. I returned home to San Diego knowing I had selected a great car and had a good deal.

Bill went the extra mile by meeting me halfway between Tustin and San Diego to deliver me the car. We signed the paperwork as I trade my 2012 Veloster. I have to say Bill made this experience one where not only would I recommend Tustin Hyundai, I would highly suggest working with Bill Farris specifically. He sells both used and new cars and truly cares about your experience and making it a positive one.

Thank you Bill and thank you Tustin Hyundai.<//Review>

Visit 3, scheduled 6k maintenance, small wing mounted to rear spoiler broken off, put in driver's seat, and 3M tape residue left on spoiler after car was "washed" and ready to pick up.

I have another visit coming up to replace a trim piece under warranty, and can only imagine something completely unrelated to the service will be broke/missing/moved when I pick it up.

The only thing preventing this from being a 1-star review is they offer food and drinks in the waiting area.

Edit: now a 1-star. This dealership is the epitome of useless customer service. One small plastic trim piece on a window, quoted 4 hours to replace, no availability during my work hours (what kind of service department closes at 3:30 during the week?). Martin from the dealership said "get here at 8 on Saturday". Get there 15 minutes early, 20 cars ahead of me, their last tech leaves at 12:30, so it's unlikely my car would even be done. Will likely have to resolve this with corporate now, and travel 10x the distance to another Hyundai dealer.</Text>< pics>

< Review>
I have a 2011 Hyundai sonata. Although I bought it at a different dealership, I always have it serviced at Tustin Hyundai. Since it's a Hyundai dealership, they can do all the required maintenance with genuine Hyundai parts. They can handle any recalls, too. There are several things I like: 1. You can schedule appointments. 2. They usually have some sort of discount coupon, which the Service Writers apply without being asked. 3. They can give you a ride or you can wait for your car in the Customer Lounge. 4. They have free coffee. 5. They wash your car before you pick it up.

I don't enjoy taking my car in for service anywhere, but at Tustin  Hyundai, I'm treated with honesty and respect which makes service appointments much more tolerable.<//Review>

Excellent Service! Have to ask for Marcos"

<userid>108296129376637921289</userid>< name>
Todd Lewis<//name>
< Date>
1494946467410< /Date>
< Rating>
5</Rating>
< Text>
A dealership experience stars by getting you to visit the lot.  The online visibility of Tustin Hyundai's inventory allowed me to find the car I wanted, and was incredibly current.  Once I arrived with my family, we were able to locate the car and look it over without being approached by a salesperson.  This isn't a complaint: I don't appreciate hard sell techniques in general, but especially intrusive behavior while I'm still appraising a vehicle.  Once I was ready to speak with a salesperson, a quick inquiry with the receptionist was all it took to be introduced to John.

John was knowledgeable about Hyundai vehicles from personal experience.  During the test drive, he related several stories of how he purchased a Hyundai, and then later came to work from them.  It was not the typical patter of "This is a great car, they're flying off of the lot, I can make you a special deal but you need to act now."  John gave me the mental space to evaluate the car.

After returning from the test drive, I let John know that I was interested in leasing the vehicle.  During our conversation John identified several discounts for which I could qualify, and of which I was not aware.  We discussed a couple of different scenarios (one with some money down, one without), and then I left with my family to grab some lunch.  John didn't put us in some interior conference room/cell and make us wait.  He called me on my cell phone and we reviewed the numbers.  I returned to the dealership later that day and we finished the lease in what felt like a very reasonable amount of time.

For me, the buying/leasing process of a car has a negative stigma about it.  My experiences with other dealerships makes me wonder if they are trying to make the process so painful that you won't want to go through it all again and you just give in.  Tustin Hyundai and John Moody were exactly the opposite: I was given the room to reach my own unforced decisions, and the process was as easy and streamlined as I could have hoped for.<//Text>

<date>1549309864167<//date>< Text>
Tustin Hyundai is part of the Tustin Autocenter, located near Tustin Marketplace.  If you need service on your Hyundai, this place is very convenient and clean.  There are many options available to you while your vehicle is being serviced.  You can wait in the customer service lounge and sip some free coffee.  Costco is just across the street if you'd like to do some shopping, as well as other retail stores, just down the street.  Shuttle transportation is available as well.

The service reps at Tustin Hyundai are friendly and professional and are happy to assist you with your service request, sometimes even telling you about the latest service special.  Wi-fi is available along with large screen television.  I've been here 3 times since I purchased my Hyundai Santa Fe and have not been disappointed with the work that has been completed.< /Text>

< Text>
Frank Joubran
Internet Sales Director

This guy was awesome. Now let me start by saying that I am not used to buying cars. I don't like HIGH pressure, and really didn't do a ton of research because it was right after a car accident and i need to get in a car asap.

Frank was a blessing from God. I looked up prices online and what i should expect and he took great care of me. He walked me through all the cars and helped pick out the one that would fit me. Being a 6'6 man there are not many out there. He didn't pressure me or hit me with any "TODAY ONLY" deals he told me exactly what i was getting and there was no surprises. Aside from not getting hunted in the shark tank.

Marco was the sales person who took me on a test drive and explained to me everything i wanted to know. He even informed me of a possible extended warranty that I might want, seeing as i drive over 150 miles a day for work, which was only presented as knowledge verses a must have.

But to be honest the best thing about it was, even thought the dealership was slammed they gave me attention like i was the only thing that mattered. Which is really impossible to find now days. After all the dealerships out there, its nice to one that gives you the information you need with out the pressure to "get it now."

I now have a beautiful car which i love and know that if anything happens i have a group of guy who have my back.

Needless to say I'm going back next time.

Thanks so much Frank.</Text>

I realized that they are very attentive and had this casual feel of just being able to come in and feel good even if you are not buying.  Frank had the same professionalism and was very helpful and honest.  He made it so simple and made me feel comfortable.  I never got the feeling of any pressure compared to the typical car sales person.  Jeff walked me the rest of the way and was very thorough and lets not talk about his personality....what a great guy.  I felt like I was just talking to a friend.  Sheryl was just the icing on the cake.  Despite it being the 15 minutes until they close,  her attitude and friendliness made it seem like she just started her shift.  This is a women that loves what she does....helping people out.</Text>

< text>
After Jaguars XJ8's and after hearing a lot of great things about the Genesis (especially electronic safety features), I decided to put my toe in the water and lease (3 years) a 2016 Genesis.  However, after 36 years of loving the fit, finish, style, power and ride of the big Jaguars, I thought there might be a tough transition and some regrets (except for the part where you have to pay "big" $$$$ for Jaguar services and repairs) after I made the move,

Wrong! Loved this car from the get go. The electronics  (especially the Heads Up Display) exceeded my expectations,  The controls are exceptionally well thought out and intuitive.  Ride, noise level and power (even with the 3.8 V-6) are exceptional.

And, at the risk of using the word twice, my investigation and leasing experience at Tustin Hyundai also was exceptional.  The folks, especially John Moody, were extremely fair and low key on the sale/lease end and super on knowledge, communication, follow up... and, especially patience.

When I say patience, as in dealing with someone who takes a lot of time to make up his mind and asks (sometimes repetitively) John Moody should change his name to Job. Very attentive without being pushy.  Frequently anticipating my questions/concerns.  Never a trace of irritation. I would rate John as one of the best salespersons I have ever dealt with or met.
